\f0\fs20 \cf0 My original attempt at creating a class diagram was a nightmare. Classes everywhere, poor spatial relation to other classes, and an overwhelming amount of unstructured information. As a result, I started to think about similar problems and what - if any - solutions there are out there to better structure this information.\ \ I decided to build an INFOGRAPHIC-esq Class diagram to allow for an easy and intuitive experience for the reader, as well as quick referencing of which Classes are contained within the TeamBox project, and their relation to one another. \ \ The end result is a combination of the typical Class diagram, with something that better resembles an "index" of all of the classes contained within the Project, yet still retains the relationships that exist between classes.\ \ Additionally, this idea is somewhat centered around the idea of embedding a linking / navigation system to allow for quick traversal of the document.}
